<br>
Outdoors I've found it easier to just have one of the rez'er take off early when the battle starts going south.  As a bard, I'm normally the one chosen since I've had endurance song up most of the fight, with full endurance sprint + Clear Path 2, a couple insta-cast on the run mem-blurs, and away I go.<br>
<br>
A difference in DAoC is that when you rez a person at a distance, that person will appear where you rez'ed from.  This is useful at times to pull a corpse from a sticky situation.  In a total group wipe out, I'm normally the first to /release, since I can get back to the group the fastest.<br>
<br>
As far a /sticky, this is very useful outside of combat as well.  You have the entire group stick to the leader, while I just /follow him, at a distance, singing Clear Path 2.  This insures all group members will be running the same speed.  It appears to be server side, and work around for the P-v-P 'joust'ing that occurred during beta.<br>
